<br>
I live to have a kick ass melee across from me in a fight, whether that be a warrior, monk, SK, ranger, or paladin. Nothing is sweeter to see than my hits land consistently, hard and swift on a mob's back while the other melee keeps its attention. And I'm sure the casters feel the same way about being able to land their spells without fear of being pounded on.<br>
<br>
To wax a little sappy, it's like a dance between me and the taunter with a mob in between and no one else exists (I don't need to pay attention to anything else because there's a kick ass cleric/healer making sure my health stays up). Even in a multi-group encounter, if you have a good assist who knows when to taunt (and providing all the damn fatties aren't in the way <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ), the rest of the melees don't matter, I can focus only on where the main tank is. That can only happen when the main tank kicks ass.<br>
<br>
No no no, do NOT nerf melees. A good, strong, capable melee ensures I can do my best damage. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  More damage from us ALL means bad mob dies faster with less mana drained and less downtime. This means more mobs for the group to kill.<br>
